2026-04-16 07:55:53 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 1 Switch Indicator', 'Control Module 2 Switch Indicator', 'Control Module 3 Switch Indicator', 'Control Module 4 Switch Indicator', 'Control Module 5 Switch Indicator', 'Control Module 6 Switch Indicator', 'Control Module 7 Switch Indicator', 'Control Module 8 Switch Indicator'] hypothesis_explanation="All eight control module switch indicator LEDs are physically missing (removed from their holders). Since each indicator LED (with its series resistor) was originally in parallel with the switch in each control module, and now both terminals are open (i.e., not shorted), this creates an open circuit in each module's control leg. Thus, although the switches are set to the ON position, there is no longer electrical continuity through the control module pathways. As a result, no current can reach the load module, and the load lamp and its indicator do not light. The root cause is the physical and non-repairable removal of the indicator LEDs, which breaks the electrical path in each module."
